# Orbital Inspect — Codex CLI Instructions

## Project Context

Orbital Inspect: satellite insurance underwriting intelligence platform.
5-agent pipeline (Classification -> Vision -> Environment -> Failure Mode -> Insurance Risk).
Backend: Python/FastAPI + SQLAlchemy async + ARQ workers.
Frontend: React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind.

## Your Role: Auditor & Verifier

You (Codex/GPT) are the architecture auditor and verifier in this multi-model workflow.

Primary responsibilities:
- Architecture audits and gap analysis (see AUDIT-GPT54.md for prior audit)
- Security review of auth, crypto, input validation, SSRF prevention
- Verification of Claude's implementations against audit recommendations
- Root cause analysis for runtime bugs
- Targeted feature builds when your domain knowledge is stronger (e.g., telemetry services)

## Other Models
- Claude Opus 4.6 (Claude Code): Primary builder — features, refactoring, tests
- Gemini 3.1 Pro (Gemini CLI): Independent validator and tie-breaker

## Attribution Rules (MANDATORY)

Every commit MUST include Co-Authored-By:

```
Co-Authored-By: Codex GPT 5.4 <noreply@openai.com>
```

If reviewing or verifying Claude's work, reference the specific commits or files in the commit body.

## Verification Protocol

When auditing, produce structured output:
1. Dimension scores (1-10) with evidence
2. Critical findings with file:line references
3. Numbered recommendations with Value/Effort ratings
4. Follow the format established in AUDIT-GPT54.md

When verifying, check:
- Do agent error handlers return degraded=True?
- Does orchestrator track evidence_gaps correctly?
- Are Pydantic model defaults safe (no silent success on failure)?
- Is Co-Authored-By attribution present on all recent commits?

## Key Files
- backend/agents/orchestrator.py — 5-stage pipeline coordinator
- backend/agents/insurance_risk_agent.py — key differentiator
- backend/services/gemini_service.py — LLM integration + parse_json_response
- backend/db/models.py — SQLAlchemy schema
- AUDIT-GPT54.md — your prior architecture audit
- AGENTS.md — multi-model collaboration log
- .agents/workflow.yaml — workflow definition
